    {
      "id": "0Spi_zTQXSpkrSi_hMN2r",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1417.648323342758,
      "y": 8009.56877499447,
      "width": 2039.398681640625,
      "height": 2340,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#e03131",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b2t",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 221846258,
      "version": 2351,
      "versionNonce": 740705375,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770404286338,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "this will mark\nreserved in \ndatabase forever\n\nif the payment success\nthen again database will be\nhit and status update to\nbooked for some user and\nwill send email to that user\nand that will be happy path\n\nbut how we will handle two\nphase if the user is not done\npayment\n\nwe need to reserve sheet for user\nfor 10 minutes\nand then confirm will call\npayment and that payment has\n10 minute countdown\nif the payment will not success\nit will be available for other\nmark DB status for this sheet\navailable.\n\nHow we will handle this ?\n\n1. we can put entry of reservedTimestamp\n    and we can make sheet status is available or \nand reserve and reservedtimestamp > 10 this makes query little complex\nbut that would work absolutely.\n\nThis is okay option by this makes our database little confusing, we have\na status or Reserve while things are not actually in a reserve status and we\nneed to keep these 2 things consistent with one another.\n We may use\ncronjob will run in every 10 minute that will check each reserve status ticket and reserveTimestamp if \ngreated than 10 minute will mark status as available. -> this approach is good for\nmid level engineers but not for senior or principle due to delta involved because\nit may be mark unreserve or available after 19 minutes instead of 19 minutes\nsuppose sheet mark reserve at 12:00\ncron run at 12:09 so it will mark available at 12:19 instead of 12:10 so we need something\nthat more realtime.\n\nTo do this we can getrid of cronjob and reservetimestamp as well, as well as reserve status\ninstead of that we can introduce a distributed lock, we will call it as ticket lock we can use\nRedis or any inmemory cache here and what it going to do is when a ticket gets reserved, instead\nof updating our ticket table and all we are going to keep track in this memory or cache itself \nand we are going to keep track of it with TTL(31:30).\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "this will mark\nreserved in \ndatabase forever\n\nif the payment success\nthen again database will be\nhit and status update to\nbooked for some user and\nwill send email to that user\nand that will be happy path\n\nbut how we will handle two\nphase if the user is not done\npayment\n\nwe need to reserve sheet for user\nfor 10 minutes\nand then confirm will call\npayment and that payment has\n10 minute countdown\nif the payment will not success\nit will be available for other\nmark DB status for this sheet\navailable.\n\nHow we will handle this ?\n\n1. we can put entry of reservedTimestamp\n    and we can make sheet status is available or \nand reserve and reservedtimestamp > 10 this makes query little complex\nbut that would work absolutely.\n\nThis is okay option by this makes our database little confusing, we have\na status or Reserve while things are not actually in a reserve status and we\nneed to keep these 2 things consistent with one another.\n We may use\ncronjob will run in every 10 minute that will check each reserve status ticket and reserveTimestamp if \ngreated than 10 minute will mark status as available. -> this approach is good for\nmid level engineers but not for senior or principle due to delta involved because\nit may be mark unreserve or available after 19 minutes instead of 19 minutes\nsuppose sheet mark reserve at 12:00\ncron run at 12:09 so it will mark available at 12:19 instead of 12:10 so we need something\nthat more realtime.\n\nTo do this we can getrid of cronjob and reservetimestamp as well, as well as reserve status\ninstead of that we can introduce a distributed lock, we will call it as ticket lock we can use\nRedis or any inmemory cache here and what it going to do is when a ticket gets reserved, instead\nof updating our ticket table and all we are going to keep track in this memory or cache itself \nand we are going to keep track of it with TTL(31:30).\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
